================================================================================
cap-y:base — MIT/Apache GRASPING ALTERNATIVES
================================================================================

These components are the commercially-clean alternatives to cuRobo and
ContactGraspNet. They are included in cap-y:base (and thus in cap-y:open and
cap-y:nvidia via inheritance). License ceiling: Meta SAM License (SAM3).

mink — differential inverse kinematics
  License : Apache 2.0
  URL     : https://github.com/tasts-robots/pink (mink variant)
  Note    : MuJoCo-based, aarch64 native. Alternative IK backend alongside pyroki.

rh56_controller — Inspire RH56DFX analytical grasp planner
  License : MIT
  URL     : https://github.com/correlllab/rh56_controller
  Copyright: 2026 Correll Lab, University of Colorado Boulder
             (Xuan Tan, William Xie, Nikolaus Correll)
  Reference: arXiv 2603.08988 — "Characterization, Analytical Planning, and
             Hybrid Force Control for the Inspire RH56DFX Hand"
  Note    : Sim2real validated MuJoCo model for width-to-grasp planning,
            hybrid speed-force control, 87% success on 300 grasps.

DemoGrasp — universal dexterous grasping from a single demonstration
  License : MIT
  URL     : https://github.com/BeingBeyond/DemoGrasp
  Reference: ICLR 2026 — "DemoGrasp: Universal Dexterous Grasping from a Single
             Demonstration"
  Note    : Inference-only by default. Supports Inspire hand natively with
            pre-trained checkpoints (95% success on DexGraspNet, 84.6% across
            diverse embodiments). Training requires IsaacGym Preview 4 (see below).

